180sumpoly" width=3D"180" height=3D"40"></strong><br>
                  <span class=3D"TimesBlack10">(where <em>n</em> =3D number=
 of sides) </span></div></td>
            </tr>
          </tbody></table></td>
        </tr>
      </tbody></table>
      <p class=3D"TimesBlack16">If you know that the polygon is a <span cla=
ss=3D"TimesDarkRed16"><strong>regular polygon</strong></span>, <br>
        you can find each interior angle by dividing by the number of sides=
.<br>
        <span class=3D"TimesBlack12">(Remember that the interior angles of =
a regular polygon are congruent.) </span></p>
